  "text": "From 1993 to 2006, in Korea, the IgG seroprevalence of clonorchiasis has been at the highest rate among cysticercosis, paragonimiasis, sparganosis, and clonorchiasis. However, because of the aforementioned cross-reactivity of clonorchiasis, it should be differentiated from other parasitic infections [CITATION_1] . Use of different antigens may be required in order to preclude cross-reactions in ELISA test.",
